1
00:02:55,008 --> 00:02:57,510
Miss Alisha, Father wants you
to eat breakfast with him.

2
00:03:02,807 --> 00:03:04,017
In a minute.

3
00:03:04,517 --> 00:03:06,603
Father says he can't stay long.

4
00:03:07,270 --> 00:03:08,188
Come on.

5
00:03:35,298 --> 00:03:36,633
I want to look for a job.

6
00:03:37,550 --> 00:03:39,719
You need more money? How much?

7
00:03:40,929 --> 00:03:42,472
I just want to be kept busy.

8
00:03:43,514 --> 00:03:46,351
I feel bored to death
when I'm just in the house

9
00:03:46,851 --> 00:03:48,311
waiting for you to come.

10
00:03:50,980 --> 00:03:53,358
Why don't you let me go
out of the country with you?

11
00:03:54,609 --> 00:03:56,110
I'm going to work.

12
00:03:59,072 --> 00:04:00,573
I could stay in a hotel

13
00:04:00,657 --> 00:04:02,408
or go for a walk on my own.

14
00:04:13,461 --> 00:04:15,838
Unless that other woman
has already asked to come along.

15
00:04:27,100 --> 00:04:29,477
I was just joking. No need to get upset.

16
00:04:48,371 --> 00:04:52,458
BASTARD

17
00:05:16,399 --> 00:05:17,859
Where is this job interview?

18
00:05:25,033 --> 00:05:26,284
This is the address.

19
00:05:30,496 --> 00:05:35,960
MULTIZONAMEDIA COMPANY

20
00:05:58,566 --> 00:06:00,068
Who have you worked for?

21
00:06:00,651 --> 00:06:02,779
I've never had a job. I've just graduated.

22
00:06:12,997 --> 00:06:14,082
Do you have something else?

23
00:06:15,625 --> 00:06:18,378
Something with a more
serious style, perhaps?

24
00:06:19,879 --> 00:06:21,464
That's all I have, sir.

25
00:06:22,131 --> 00:06:24,300
But this is my style.

26
00:06:31,099 --> 00:06:32,392
Twenty years old.

27
00:06:34,644 --> 00:06:35,728
So young.

28
00:06:40,149 --> 00:06:41,067
Hello?

29
00:06:46,572 --> 00:06:47,949
Okay, I'll take it outside.

30
00:06:58,793 --> 00:06:59,836
Yes?

31
00:07:01,421 --> 00:07:02,547
Oh. Hello, sir.

32
00:07:04,048 --> 00:07:05,049
Oh yes.

33
00:07:06,342 --> 00:07:07,468
What can I do for you?

34
00:07:14,434 --> 00:07:15,476
Is that so?

35
00:07:17,728 --> 00:07:18,688
All right, sir.

36
00:07:22,358 --> 00:07:23,943
No problem. Good day, sir.

37
00:07:33,578 --> 00:07:34,871
When can you start work?

38
00:07:35,705 --> 00:07:36,664
I got the job?

39
00:07:37,665 --> 00:07:39,500
-Yes.
-Why?

40
00:07:40,293 --> 00:07:41,210
What do you mean?

41
00:07:41,711 --> 00:07:44,922
A moment ago,
you were not sure about my ability.

42
00:07:46,257 --> 00:07:47,467
I never said that.

43
00:07:47,550 --> 00:07:49,010
Who was on the phone?

44
00:07:53,473 --> 00:07:55,600
I need a designer as soon as possible.

45
00:07:55,683 --> 00:07:57,351
And I like your portfolio.

46
00:07:58,144 --> 00:08:01,272
So I'll try to ignore
your impolite attitude,

47
00:08:01,355 --> 00:08:03,649
asking me who I was
talking to on the phone.

48
00:08:21,459 --> 00:08:22,960
So, what do you think, Alisha?

49
00:08:37,850 --> 00:08:39,519
Yes, sir. Okay.

50
00:08:40,853 --> 00:08:41,938
Give me your phone.

51
00:08:44,357 --> 00:08:47,443
MISTER HARYO

52
00:08:55,451 --> 00:08:57,203
<i>Multizonamedia. How may I help you?</i>

53
00:08:58,538 --> 00:09:00,581
We're going home. Now.

54
00:09:53,968 --> 00:09:55,761
You look really pretty, Alisha.

55
00:10:59,200 --> 00:11:00,910
No one believes me.

56
00:11:03,162 --> 00:11:04,830
But I know your father's plan.

57
00:11:13,756 --> 00:11:14,924
Look, Alisha.

58
00:11:16,592 --> 00:11:19,720
This is what he is going to use
to kill me.

59
00:11:35,695 --> 00:11:38,322
We were confused
about what name to give you.

60
00:11:44,161 --> 00:11:45,371
Ajeng,

61
00:11:47,873 --> 00:11:48,958
Kirana,

62
00:11:50,209 --> 00:11:51,210
or Alisha.

63
00:11:56,424 --> 00:11:57,758
Then…

64
00:11:59,719 --> 00:12:01,887
your father gave in
and agreed to my choice.

65
00:12:05,057 --> 00:12:07,017
But since your father met that woman,

66
00:12:07,101 --> 00:12:09,270
he's become her dog.

67
00:12:13,232 --> 00:12:15,818
She tells your father to kill me

68
00:12:16,318 --> 00:12:18,654
after your little brother is born.

69
00:12:22,908 --> 00:12:24,994
But Mommy won't let that happen.

70
00:12:27,413 --> 00:12:29,123
Your brother will never be born.

71
00:12:32,626 --> 00:12:34,712
You two will…

72
00:12:36,672 --> 00:12:38,299
never be hers.

73
00:12:42,344 --> 00:12:45,431
There's only one way,
Alisha, my lovely daughter.

74
00:12:49,310 --> 00:12:50,269
You,

75
00:12:51,479 --> 00:12:52,772
your little brother,

76
00:12:54,774 --> 00:12:55,941
and Mommy,

77
00:12:57,443 --> 00:12:59,278
we will be together again in Heaven.

78
00:13:13,000 --> 00:13:15,294
Mommy can't do it, Alisha.

79
00:13:17,505 --> 00:13:19,548
Mommy really can't do it!

80
00:13:23,928 --> 00:13:26,222
You have to do it yourself.

81
00:13:26,305 --> 00:13:27,515
After me.

82
00:13:35,648 --> 00:13:38,234
Everything happens for a reason, Alisha.

83
00:14:59,064 --> 00:15:01,483
Who's the guy cleaning the pool?

84
00:15:02,818 --> 00:15:06,155
He's replacing Mr. Pono
while he's on holiday.

85
00:15:08,240 --> 00:15:09,366
Where is he from?

86
00:15:10,034 --> 00:15:14,204
He said that he sometimes
works for Mrs. Pono.

87
00:15:15,080 --> 00:15:18,250
She owns a food stall in Block S.

88
00:15:19,043 --> 00:15:20,169
Block S?

89
00:15:20,252 --> 00:15:24,006
There are lots of roadside stalls there.

90
00:15:24,548 --> 00:15:29,303
They sell dumplings, satay, fried rice.

91
00:15:29,845 --> 00:15:32,056
They're all in Block S.

92
00:16:22,147 --> 00:16:25,234
Miss Tuti! I'm going home!

93
00:16:25,317 --> 00:16:26,527
Wait a minute!

94
00:16:49,466 --> 00:16:51,927
-What time will you come tomorrow?
-In the morning.

95
00:16:52,428 --> 00:16:53,554
Thanks, Miss Tuti.

96
00:18:31,443 --> 00:18:32,361
Miss Tuti!

97
00:18:32,861 --> 00:18:33,987
I'm going home!

98
00:18:34,822 --> 00:18:35,697
Hold on!

99
00:18:53,549 --> 00:18:54,383
Thanks.

100
00:19:31,003 --> 00:19:33,046
Miss Tuti, where's the pool cleaner?

101
00:19:33,672 --> 00:19:35,632
He doesn't work here anymore.

102
00:19:35,716 --> 00:19:37,301
Mr. Pono will be back tomorrow.

103
00:19:39,261 --> 00:19:40,220
Why do you ask?

104
00:19:45,184 --> 00:19:46,643
No reason.

105
00:20:24,640 --> 00:20:26,934
Mr. Bambang, I'm going out.

106
00:20:34,942 --> 00:20:37,861
Mr. Bambang, do you know
a place to eat called Block S?

107
00:20:41,031 --> 00:20:42,115
You want to go there?

108
00:21:08,225 --> 00:21:12,562
Okay, good afternoon.
You're with us again.

109
00:21:13,438 --> 00:21:16,775
This is for the guests under the tent.

110
00:21:17,818 --> 00:21:20,862
We will entertain you
with some of our songs.

111
00:21:29,454 --> 00:21:30,998
One orange juice, please.

112
00:22:59,461 --> 00:23:00,420
Yes?

113
00:23:01,088 --> 00:23:02,339
Are you going to be long?

114
00:23:03,006 --> 00:23:05,592
Yes, I am. No need to wait for me.
You can go home.

115
00:23:06,676 --> 00:23:07,844
I'll just wait.

116
00:23:27,447 --> 00:23:29,449
-Hey, Bar!
-What's up?

117
00:23:30,659 --> 00:23:32,536
-Where have you been?
-Hey, ma'am.

118
00:23:35,122 --> 00:23:36,706
I've been working.

119
00:23:37,499 --> 00:23:40,794
-No wonder you brought an envelope. Cool!
-Tacky.

120
00:23:42,170 --> 00:23:44,089
-Come on. Buy us some drinks.
-Thanks, ma'am.

121
00:23:44,172 --> 00:23:45,215
See you, guys.

122
00:23:57,769 --> 00:24:00,439
Block S to the left.

123
00:24:00,522 --> 00:24:01,857
Let's go.

124
00:25:02,751 --> 00:25:06,379
You're still studying?

125
00:25:07,339 --> 00:25:10,008
I'll be done in a moment.

126
00:25:10,091 --> 00:25:11,051
Let's eat.

127
00:25:12,844 --> 00:25:13,803
What did you get?

128
00:25:14,846 --> 00:25:15,805
This.

129
00:25:16,848 --> 00:25:18,225
Gado-gado again?

130
00:25:20,810 --> 00:25:22,854
Don't worry. When I'm rich,

131
00:25:22,938 --> 00:25:25,440
I'll take you to expensive restaurants
every night.

132
00:25:26,191 --> 00:25:27,567
I'm just kidding, dear.

133
00:25:27,651 --> 00:25:30,695
As long as I'm with you,
I don't care if I eat at all.

134
00:25:31,196 --> 00:25:33,281
Yeah, right. You're so cheesy.

135
00:25:33,365 --> 00:25:38,245
FOR RENT

136
00:25:40,038 --> 00:25:43,500
Miss Alisha, I was scared to death.

137
00:25:43,583 --> 00:25:45,627
Where have you been?

138
00:25:45,710 --> 00:25:47,379
I just wanted to be alone.

139
00:25:47,462 --> 00:25:48,588
Don't do that.

140
00:25:49,089 --> 00:25:51,174
I'll get in trouble with your father.

141
00:25:51,258 --> 00:25:53,552
If he gets mad, just say it's my fault.

142
00:25:58,515 --> 00:26:01,351
Wherever and whenever you
want to go out, I can take you.

143
00:26:01,434 --> 00:26:02,519
You just need to ask.

144
00:26:02,602 --> 00:26:04,437
I'm bored going out with you.

145
00:26:05,188 --> 00:26:08,275
Bored or not, that's my job.

146
00:26:08,775 --> 00:26:12,445
What are you getting mad for?
Have you forgotten who's the boss here?

147
00:26:12,529 --> 00:26:14,155
Now, you listen.

148
00:26:14,239 --> 00:26:16,908
Your father is my boss, not you.

149
00:26:17,492 --> 00:26:19,578
My job is to look after you!

150
00:26:20,662 --> 00:26:22,455
Okay, that's enough.

151
00:26:22,539 --> 00:26:27,586
Miss, it's fine if you don't
want to go out with Bambang.

152
00:26:27,669 --> 00:26:29,629
Next time, let me accompany you.

153
00:26:29,713 --> 00:26:32,215
You want to go with her?
She'll go off by herself in a minute.

154
00:26:32,299 --> 00:26:34,259
You can't even look after a girl.

155
00:26:34,342 --> 00:26:36,511
Weren't you a private detective before?

156
00:27:46,414 --> 00:27:47,666
These are for you.

157
00:27:48,708 --> 00:27:50,085
I'm sorry about last night.

158
00:28:07,852 --> 00:28:09,312
But these are expensive.

159
00:28:09,396 --> 00:28:11,106
That's okay for once in a while.

160
00:28:17,570 --> 00:28:19,656
You still want to take me around, right?

161
00:28:20,490 --> 00:28:22,784
I promise I won't go off by myself again.

162
00:28:48,059 --> 00:28:50,478
How long are you going to be
in the music studio?

163
00:28:51,104 --> 00:28:52,772
Only until the afternoon.

164
00:28:52,856 --> 00:28:55,650
Why don't you come inside
and watch me practice?

165
00:29:08,079 --> 00:29:11,291
Please carry these.
My friends are waiting.

166
00:29:11,916 --> 00:29:14,085
Later, come back to take my cello.

167
00:30:36,376 --> 00:30:37,377
Please come in.

168
00:30:40,088 --> 00:30:40,922
Thank you.

169
00:30:52,642 --> 00:30:56,354
Pecel!

170
00:30:57,188 --> 00:31:01,359
Pecel!

171
00:31:38,813 --> 00:31:41,024
Who did you tell your parents
you lived with?

172
00:31:41,524 --> 00:31:43,318
With no one.

173
00:31:43,818 --> 00:31:44,694
I'm not crazy.

174
00:31:45,528 --> 00:31:47,989
They think <i>samenleven</i>
means premarital cohabitation.

175
00:31:48,489 --> 00:31:50,742
When it only means to live together.

176
00:31:50,825 --> 00:31:53,703
It's not just couples
who live together before marriage.

177
00:31:55,538 --> 00:31:58,416
Different races living in the same country
are also <i>samenleven</i>.

178
00:31:59,292 --> 00:32:00,793
And your point is?

179
00:32:01,461 --> 00:32:03,004
My point is

180
00:32:03,087 --> 00:32:07,467
Indonesians have many ways of giving
negative connotations to many things.

181
00:32:08,426 --> 00:32:09,469
Example?

182
00:32:10,511 --> 00:32:12,972
Well, we live together
because we love each other.

183
00:32:14,098 --> 00:32:15,350
Who's in love?

184
00:32:16,559 --> 00:32:18,061
Why are you such a pain today?

185
00:32:58,851 --> 00:32:59,978
What's up?

186
00:33:00,979 --> 00:33:03,231
Right. My friend's studying.
She has an exam tomorrow.

187
00:33:03,314 --> 00:33:04,732
So I came over.

188
00:33:05,525 --> 00:33:06,818
I'm scared she'll get pissed.

189
00:33:07,652 --> 00:33:08,903
If she gets pissed, ouch.

190
00:33:11,906 --> 00:33:12,824
So?

191
00:33:16,035 --> 00:33:17,245
Oh, right. Sorry.

192
00:33:21,249 --> 00:33:22,542
What are you doing?

193
00:33:23,543 --> 00:33:25,378
I can't drain water out of the sink.

194
00:33:28,756 --> 00:33:29,674
Can I take a look?

195
00:33:55,783 --> 00:33:56,993
Try and open the faucet.

196
00:34:04,125 --> 00:34:05,418
You need to tighten it.

197
00:34:05,918 --> 00:34:08,004
Hitting it won't do any good.

198
00:34:20,266 --> 00:34:21,768
The water here is quite dirty.

199
00:34:23,936 --> 00:34:26,647
But I have a spare filter.

200
00:34:28,983 --> 00:34:29,901
Do you want it?

201
00:34:38,076 --> 00:34:39,243
I'll go and get it.

202
00:34:41,412 --> 00:34:42,622
Can I come with you?

203
00:34:43,164 --> 00:34:45,666
I'd like to see
what the other rooms look like.

204
00:35:01,474 --> 00:35:04,393
Renta, we've got a new neighbor.

205
00:35:05,103 --> 00:35:07,021
Hi. I'm Renta.

206
00:35:08,147 --> 00:35:09,065
Mia.

207
00:35:13,277 --> 00:35:14,612
I haven't introduced myself.

208
00:35:15,822 --> 00:35:16,656
I'm Bari.

209
00:35:20,451 --> 00:35:22,245
Bari told me you're studying for an exam.

210
00:35:22,328 --> 00:35:24,372
I'd better go.
I don't want to disturb you.

211
00:35:24,455 --> 00:35:25,414
No, not at all.

212
00:35:25,498 --> 00:35:29,252
If Bari sees someone reading,
he automatically thinks they're studying.

213
00:35:32,171 --> 00:35:33,506
What are you reading?

214
00:35:33,589 --> 00:35:35,258
It's just a coursebook.

215
00:35:36,676 --> 00:35:38,177
Renta is a budding psychologist.

216
00:35:40,555 --> 00:35:42,557
You never read the psychology book
I bought you.

217
00:35:43,141 --> 00:35:44,851
That's just pop psychology, Bari.

218
00:35:44,934 --> 00:35:46,894
It doesn't have anything to do
with what I study.

219
00:35:46,978 --> 00:35:47,937
What book?

220
00:35:48,646 --> 00:35:50,523
You know, self-help.

221
00:35:50,606 --> 00:35:52,984
How would I know?
It came from the psychology shelf.

222
00:35:53,067 --> 00:35:54,735
Read it, then.

223
00:35:54,819 --> 00:35:55,695
I can't be bothered.

224
00:35:55,778 --> 00:35:58,364
-A writer who doesn't like reading.
-I read.

225
00:35:58,447 --> 00:36:00,366
You never finish.

226
00:36:00,449 --> 00:36:04,704
Every good book I read makes me jealous

227
00:36:04,787 --> 00:36:06,706
and makes me want to write.

228
00:36:06,789 --> 00:36:08,040
You're a writer?

229
00:36:08,124 --> 00:36:11,669
Just like reading, he never finishes it!

230
00:36:12,170 --> 00:36:14,881
One day, my book will be released,

231
00:36:14,964 --> 00:36:18,176
and it'll have "New York Times Bestseller"
written on the cover.

232
00:36:18,718 --> 00:36:19,927
You just wait,

233
00:36:21,053 --> 00:36:22,013
Miss Shrink.

234
00:36:22,555 --> 00:36:23,681
Are you at university?

235
00:36:24,599 --> 00:36:25,558
No.

236
00:36:29,729 --> 00:36:31,355
Who likes rabbits?

237
00:36:31,439 --> 00:36:32,481
I do.

238
00:36:33,357 --> 00:36:34,692
Oh, hold on.

239
00:36:42,575 --> 00:36:44,076
Where did you steal this from?

240
00:36:44,160 --> 00:36:45,578
From a rich person's house.

241
00:36:45,661 --> 00:36:47,288
They can just buy another one.

242
00:36:49,290 --> 00:36:50,583
It's cute.

243
00:36:51,250 --> 00:36:54,212
Psychologists shouldn't like
childish stuff like that.

244
00:36:56,672 --> 00:36:57,798
It's so cute.

245
00:36:58,633 --> 00:37:00,218
-Thank you.
-Yeah.

246
00:37:02,220 --> 00:37:04,013
Are you friends or family?

247
00:37:54,855 --> 00:37:56,357
Oh shit! I am late!

248
00:37:57,733 --> 00:38:01,445
Relax. The traffic's not bad at this hour.

249
00:38:02,989 --> 00:38:05,324
By the way, our money
has nearly all gone, Bar.

250
00:38:05,866 --> 00:38:07,034
All right!

251
00:38:07,785 --> 00:38:09,120
Off you go!

252
00:40:46,527 --> 00:40:47,736
Wow. That sounded great.

253
00:40:49,697 --> 00:40:51,407
-Cello?
-Yes.

254
00:40:54,827 --> 00:40:55,786
Are you a musician?

255
00:40:55,870 --> 00:40:57,371
No. It's just a hobby.

256
00:40:59,623 --> 00:41:00,833
Is it difficult to play?

257
00:41:01,417 --> 00:41:02,418
Have a go.

258
00:41:12,344 --> 00:41:13,262
Sorry.

259
00:41:16,348 --> 00:41:17,558
Place your hand like this.

260
00:41:33,157 --> 00:41:34,241
It sounds bad now.

261
00:41:40,122 --> 00:41:41,749
You used a cassette, didn't you?

262
00:41:51,967 --> 00:41:53,093
Why did you move here?

263
00:41:55,471 --> 00:41:57,389
My parents died a long time ago.

264
00:41:57,890 --> 00:41:59,433
I lived with my aunt.

265
00:42:00,059 --> 00:42:02,102
I felt it was time for me to move out.

266
00:42:02,937 --> 00:42:03,979
Where do you work?

267
00:42:05,105 --> 00:42:07,233
I am still looking working for work. You?

268
00:42:09,109 --> 00:42:10,861
I'll do any work.

269
00:42:11,987 --> 00:42:15,366
Paint walls or be a driver.

270
00:42:20,120 --> 00:42:21,830
Why did you choose to live here?

271
00:42:24,124 --> 00:42:25,334
I had a mate

272
00:42:26,168 --> 00:42:27,920
who told me
