Her name is Mrs. Dirah.

540
01:11:03,259 --> 01:11:04,677
You may have never met her.

541
01:11:05,219 --> 01:11:06,804
The lady with all the cats?

542
01:11:07,554 --> 01:11:09,848
Bari told me. How did she die?

543
01:11:10,349 --> 01:11:13,018
She jumped from the seventh floor.
Her cats were gone.

544
01:11:13,978 --> 01:11:16,730
A few of them were found dead
inside the first floor's garbage bin.

545
01:11:18,065 --> 01:11:19,733
Someone must have thrown them there.

546
01:11:20,776 --> 01:11:22,111
Who would do such a thing?

547
01:11:23,779 --> 01:11:25,906
There are a lot
of sick people around here.

548
01:11:32,246 --> 01:11:33,247
Hey.

549
01:11:36,417 --> 01:11:37,501
Where were you?

550
01:11:38,085 --> 01:11:40,963
I told you. I was at a friend's,
then I went shopping.

551
01:11:41,046 --> 01:11:43,215
Why are you interrogating me?

552
01:11:46,218 --> 01:11:49,305
If you think it was me
who threw the cats into the garbage bin,

553
01:11:49,388 --> 01:11:50,639
you're out of your mind!

554
01:11:50,723 --> 01:11:52,808
You're eaten up by your own fiction.

555
01:11:53,726 --> 01:11:54,810
Well, no.

556
01:11:56,562 --> 01:11:58,731
It's weird.
It seems this is all a coincidence.

557
01:11:59,690 --> 01:12:00,774
Yesterday, Rudi died.

558
01:12:01,275 --> 01:12:02,276
Now, Mrs. Dirah.

559
01:12:03,819 --> 01:12:06,572
And everything happened
after I showed you my stories.

560
01:13:26,944 --> 01:13:29,196
I brought you this. I found another one.

561
01:13:31,573 --> 01:13:35,661
But I am not going to
collect them anymore.

562
01:13:35,744 --> 01:13:38,455
-Why?
-For detachment.

563
01:13:38,539 --> 01:13:39,581
What do you mean?

564
01:13:40,082 --> 01:13:42,501
It's not good getting
too attached to something.

565
01:13:42,584 --> 01:13:45,170
There has got to be a separation
so you don't depend on it too much.

566
01:13:45,254 --> 01:13:48,090
Anyway, they're just statues
and bunny dolls.

567
01:13:50,092 --> 01:13:51,009
Hi, Bar.

568
01:13:52,136 --> 01:13:53,095
Hi, Mi.

569
01:13:57,015 --> 01:13:58,851
Okay then, I'd better be going.

570
01:13:58,934 --> 01:14:00,853
I just wanted to give you this.

571
01:14:07,276 --> 01:14:08,235
What's going on?

572
01:14:10,362 --> 01:14:11,947
What's going on between you and Mia?

573
01:14:12,030 --> 01:14:13,115
What do you mean?

574
01:14:15,909 --> 01:14:19,246
I'm not that stupid, Bari.

575
01:14:19,329 --> 01:14:21,373
I know there's something going on here.

576
01:14:29,548 --> 01:14:30,591
You swear?

577
01:14:34,887 --> 01:14:36,555
I just don't like the girl.

578
01:14:38,682 --> 01:14:39,892
Why?

579
01:14:40,726 --> 01:14:42,478
Don't you think she is a bit weird?

580
01:14:45,314 --> 01:14:47,232
Why does she give you those dolls?

581
01:14:48,358 --> 01:14:50,486
It's like she's looking for your sympathy.

582
01:14:51,320 --> 01:14:53,155
You're being oversensitive.

583
01:14:54,198 --> 01:14:55,532
Maybe writer's block?

584
01:14:56,617 --> 01:14:57,534
I don't know.

585
01:15:00,245 --> 01:15:04,541
It feels so cruel to write
about these sorts of events.

586
01:16:44,349 --> 01:16:45,601
In a minute.

587
01:17:21,928 --> 01:17:22,971
Who is it, Bar?

588
01:17:26,058 --> 01:17:27,684
No one. Just kids playing around.

589
01:17:30,062 --> 01:17:32,272
Just twist their ears if you catch them.

590
01:17:32,773 --> 01:17:33,815
All right.

591
01:17:39,196 --> 01:17:41,031
Renta, I'm going out for cigarettes!

592
01:18:38,672 --> 01:18:40,549
Bari, can I talk to you for a second?

593
01:18:47,013 --> 01:18:48,223
Renta, you better go in.

594
01:19:18,253 --> 01:19:19,713
What do you want to talk about?

595
01:19:21,506 --> 01:19:23,467
I want to apologize for yesterday.

596
01:19:23,550 --> 01:19:25,594
I don't know what I was thinking.

597
01:19:28,013 --> 01:19:30,056
-What do you want from me?
-I love you.

598
01:19:39,941 --> 01:19:41,693
I don't want anything from you.

599
01:19:41,777 --> 01:19:43,403
I'm not asking for anything.

600
01:19:44,029 --> 01:19:45,906
I just wanted to let you know.

601
01:19:54,790 --> 01:19:55,957
Bari, wait.

602
01:19:56,625 --> 01:19:58,126
Please accompany me for a while.

603
01:19:58,210 --> 01:20:00,212
I can't, Mi. I better go inside.

604
01:20:01,129 --> 01:20:02,380
I want to tell Renta.

605
01:20:02,464 --> 01:20:03,590
About what?

606
01:20:04,257 --> 01:20:06,718
-I want to tell her the truth.
-She doesn't need to know.

607
01:20:07,344 --> 01:20:09,262
-Of course she needs to know!
-But why?

608
01:20:09,346 --> 01:20:11,723
Why? Because I love her!

609
01:20:13,809 --> 01:20:15,936
And I wish for a miracle
that she will forgive me.

610
01:20:16,436 --> 01:20:20,065
You should be more concerned
about your stories, not her.

611
01:20:21,358 --> 01:20:22,818
I hate those stories.

612
01:20:23,527 --> 01:20:24,903
The endings are so cliché.

613
01:20:26,112 --> 01:20:27,864
And what's more cliché is my own story.

614
01:20:27,948 --> 01:20:30,116
A guy who already has a girlfriend
getting involved with…

615
01:20:30,200 --> 01:20:31,326
A what?

616
01:20:32,619 --> 01:20:33,620
A psychopath?

617
01:20:37,082 --> 01:20:38,542
I am not a psychopath.

618
01:20:40,836 --> 01:20:43,129
From now on, I won't bother you anymore.

619
01:20:45,674 --> 01:20:47,759
You don't need to tell Renta anything.

620
01:20:48,260 --> 01:20:50,178
Everything will go back
to how it used to be.

621
01:21:08,738 --> 01:21:09,656
Renta!

622
01:21:10,156 --> 01:21:11,992
Can you leave me alone, please?

623
01:21:12,701 --> 01:21:13,618
Ta.

624
01:21:14,160 --> 01:21:15,787
I will do anything for you.

625
01:21:16,872 --> 01:21:17,914
Anything.

626
01:21:19,749 --> 01:21:21,293
If it means that you'll forgive me.

627
01:21:23,003 --> 01:21:24,212
I don't know about that.

628
01:21:25,714 --> 01:21:27,507
But please leave me alone for now.

629
01:21:29,634 --> 01:21:30,552
Please.

630
01:22:14,930 --> 01:22:18,433
I AM SORRY, BAR.

631
01:22:18,516 --> 01:22:21,645
I HAVE TO GO. I JUST WISH FOR ONE THING.

632
01:22:21,728 --> 01:22:24,105
FINISH YOUR STORIES. RENTA.

633
01:22:45,627 --> 01:22:49,297
<i>The number you are calling</i>
<i>is not available right now.</i>

634
01:23:00,767 --> 01:23:03,436
<i>The number you are calling</i>
<i>is not available right now.</i>

635
01:23:08,650 --> 01:23:11,403
<i>The number you are calling</i>
<i>is not available right now.</i>

636
01:24:29,939 --> 01:24:31,566
<i>I'm sitting on this mat.</i>

637
01:24:33,026 --> 01:24:35,653
<i>The same mat</i>
<i>I've been sitting on for five years.</i>

638
01:24:37,280 --> 01:24:40,784
<i>Here, opposite my room.</i>

639
01:24:41,284 --> 01:24:43,578
<i>No, not my room.</i>

640
01:24:44,287 --> 01:24:46,873
<i>If I say this is my room,</i>

641
01:24:46,956 --> 01:24:49,959
<i>It means that I lose and they won.</i>

642
01:24:52,087 --> 01:24:54,506
<i>They burned my house five years ago.</i>

643
01:24:55,298 --> 01:24:57,967
<i>They took our land to build this flat.</i>

644
01:24:59,385 --> 01:25:01,096
<i>They didn't give us money.</i>

645
01:25:02,097 --> 01:25:05,100
<i>Just this room on the seventh floor</i>

646
01:25:05,183 --> 01:25:08,019
<i>that will never replace my old house.</i>

647
01:25:09,395 --> 01:25:11,731
<i>Not because it was a big house,</i>

648
01:25:12,315 --> 01:25:14,567
<i>but I built it with my own hands.</i>

649
01:25:15,693 --> 01:25:16,778
<i>My masterpiece.</i>

650
01:25:18,071 --> 01:25:20,532
<i>The only masterpiece I ever had.</i>

651
01:25:22,158 --> 01:25:24,702
<i>My marriage is clearly not a masterpiece.</i>

652
01:25:25,578 --> 01:25:26,746
<i>My wife is dumb.</i>

653
01:25:27,247 --> 01:25:28,373
<i>I am dumb.</i>

654
01:25:29,415 --> 01:25:32,085
<i>We don't even know how to communicate.</i>

655
01:25:33,545 --> 01:25:35,296
<i>We didn't go to school.</i>

656
01:25:36,089 --> 01:25:37,423
<i>Maybe that's why</i>

657
01:25:38,508 --> 01:25:40,635
<i>my three kids are not masterpieces either.</i>

658
01:25:42,637 --> 01:25:45,098
<i>My eldest son is missing now.</i>

659
01:25:46,558 --> 01:25:49,644
<i>He stabbed someone to death</i>
<i>when he was 14 years old.</i>

660
01:25:50,562 --> 01:25:54,607
<i>I don't know if he's already free</i>

661
01:25:55,233 --> 01:25:56,109
<i>or still in jail.</i>

662
01:25:56,609 --> 01:25:59,237
<i>My second son always stays in the house.</i>

663
01:25:59,737 --> 01:26:03,032
<i>He never leaves the house,</i>
<i>never hangs out,</i>

664
01:26:04,033 --> 01:26:05,451
<i>or does anything.</i>

665
01:26:06,327 --> 01:26:08,830
<i>He doesn't work, doesn't go to school.</i>

666
01:26:09,330 --> 01:26:11,791
<i>None of my kids go to school.</i>

667
01:26:12,500 --> 01:26:13,877
<i>Maybe that's why.</i>

668
01:26:15,211 --> 01:26:17,964
<i>My third kid is a daughter.</i>

669
01:26:19,174 --> 01:26:21,926
<i>Maybe she's the only one</i>
<i>that's close to a masterpiece.</i>

670
01:26:23,261 --> 01:26:25,889
<i>Her smile is charming. Her skin is fair.</i>

671
01:26:25,972 --> 01:26:28,641
<i>Even though she's never had a facial.</i>

672
01:26:29,142 --> 01:26:30,351
<i>A facial!</i>

673
01:26:30,435 --> 01:26:32,478
<i>Our family has to struggle just for food.</i>

674
01:26:32,979 --> 01:26:34,939
<i>She'll be home soon.</i>

675
01:26:36,274 --> 01:26:37,984
<i>She has found her soulmate.</i>

676
01:26:39,194 --> 01:26:42,322
<i>A biker who also owns a cart</i>
<i>to sell fried snacks.</i>

677
01:26:42,989 --> 01:26:44,324
<i>She will be somebody.</i>

678
01:26:45,825 --> 01:26:47,243
<i>Her life will be better.</i>

679
01:26:48,244 --> 01:26:52,248
<i>Today, her boyfriend and his family</i>
<i>are coming to propose to my daughter.</i>

680
01:26:53,458 --> 01:26:56,294
<i>Since morning, my wife has tried</i>
<i>to get me to enter the room.</i>

681
01:26:56,377 --> 01:26:59,380
Why don't you come in for a while?
It's for your daughter's sake!

682
01:26:59,881 --> 01:27:03,551
When their family has gone,
you can sit there again!

683
01:27:06,471 --> 01:27:08,431
Or go somewhere else

684
01:27:08,514 --> 01:27:11,226
until they've all gone,
then you can come back.

685
01:27:11,726 --> 01:27:13,645
<i>They'll never understand.</i>

686
01:27:14,771 --> 01:27:16,356
<i>No one can.</i>

687
01:27:17,106 --> 01:27:18,816
<i>Except for my daughter.</i>

688
01:27:19,776 --> 01:27:21,694
<i>She's the only one who understands me.</i>

689
01:27:22,362 --> 01:27:24,489
<i>I'm sure she won't force me</i>
<i>to come inside.</i>

690
01:27:26,157 --> 01:27:27,742
<i>I am sure she won't be ashamed.</i>

691
01:27:29,619 --> 01:27:31,329
<i>The time is getting near.</i>

692
01:27:31,412 --> 01:27:33,581
<i>She'll be home very soon.</i>

693
01:27:34,082 --> 01:27:36,251
<i>I can't wait to see her!</i>

694
01:27:36,751 --> 01:27:39,629
<i>She just had her first visit</i>
<i>to the hairdresser.</i>

695
01:27:42,548 --> 01:27:43,466
<i>There she is.</i>

696
01:27:46,094 --> 01:27:47,804
<i>Wow. She looks so pretty.</i>

697
01:27:48,805 --> 01:27:50,598
<i>She's prettier than usual.</i>

698
01:27:51,391 --> 01:27:53,017
<i>She's my masterpiece, after all.</i>

699
01:27:54,102 --> 01:27:55,770
<i>She understands me like no other.</i>

700
01:27:56,688 --> 01:27:59,899
<i>I'm sure she won't mind</i>
<i>if I stay on my mat.</i>

701
01:27:59,983 --> 01:28:01,901
Father, you're still out here?

702
01:28:02,402 --> 01:28:06,072
Are you trying to embarrass me?
Do you want my future in-laws to run away?

703
01:28:07,949 --> 01:28:10,076
Can you force that old man to come inside?

704
01:28:18,209 --> 01:28:21,587
<i>I am sure she is acting like that</i>
<i>because today is her big day.</i>

705
01:28:23,256 --> 01:28:24,799
<i>I can't be selfish.</i>

706
01:28:27,260 --> 01:28:28,886
<i>I have to do something.</i>

707
01:28:30,263 --> 01:28:31,597
<i>But what?</i>

708
01:28:33,099 --> 01:28:36,185
<i>If I go in, it means I lost,</i>

709
01:28:37,270 --> 01:28:38,646
<i>and they won.</i>

710
01:28:40,940 --> 01:28:42,608
<i>What should I do?</i>

711
01:28:43,818 --> 01:28:44,777
<i>What?</i>

712
01:28:46,404 --> 01:28:48,197
<i>My body feels so weak.</i>

713
01:28:49,157 --> 01:28:51,242
<i>I can't walk too far.</i>

714
01:28:52,160 --> 01:28:56,331
<i>If I'm still here, they would see me</i>

715
01:28:57,081 --> 01:28:59,292
<i>and my daughter will be ashamed.</i>

716
01:29:01,294 --> 01:29:02,920
<i>What should I do?</i>

717
01:29:04,589 --> 01:29:05,590
<i>What?</i>

718
01:29:10,595 --> 01:29:12,638
<i>This railing is not too high.</i>

719
01:29:13,931 --> 01:29:15,308
<i>Maybe I could climb on it.</i>

720
01:29:16,517 --> 01:29:19,479
<i>My body is very light anyway.</i>

721
01:29:26,861 --> 01:29:27,779
<i>Hop.</i>

722
01:29:29,280 --> 01:29:31,074
<i>I am on top of it now.</i>

723
01:29:36,120 --> 01:29:37,080
<i>One.</i>

724
01:29:38,956 --> 01:29:40,249
<i>Two.</i>

725
01:29:42,335 --> 01:29:43,252
<i>Three.</i>

726
01:29:49,217 --> 01:29:51,803
<i>Everything is in slow motion.</i>

727
01:29:53,513 --> 01:29:54,555
<i>I am flying.</i>

728
01:29:56,349 --> 01:29:58,684
<i>Maybe because my body is very light.</i>

729
01:30:00,395 --> 01:30:01,604
<i>Did I lose?</i>

730
01:30:03,398 --> 01:30:04,482
<i>Or did I win?</i>

731
01:30:07,777 --> 01:30:11,447
<i>All that I know is no one will miss me.</i>

732
01:30:50,778 --> 01:30:53,364
PERPENSI BND COOPERATIVE STORE

733
01:30:58,870 --> 01:31:00,121
<i>Where were you?</i>

734
01:31:04,709 --> 01:31:06,085
You know something happened?

735
01:31:09,797 --> 01:31:12,049
Tell me you've got nothing to do with it.

736
01:31:14,469 --> 01:31:16,429
I've been out all afternoon, Bari.

737
01:32:41,889 --> 01:32:43,099
I want to talk to you.

738
01:32:45,518 --> 01:32:47,895
-There is nothing to talk about.
-Yes, there is.

739
01:32:52,441 --> 01:32:54,193
Okay, let's talk.

740
01:32:54,277 --> 01:32:55,570
We can't talk here.

741
01:32:57,196 --> 01:32:59,824
There is something important
that I need to show you.

742
01:33:03,619 --> 01:33:05,204
Come with me, please.

743
01:33:06,205 --> 01:33:08,082
Then you will understand why.

744
01:33:13,004 --> 01:33:14,797
Come with me for a moment.

745
01:33:15,339 --> 01:33:17,425
Trust me. I promise you,

746
01:33:19,010 --> 01:33:20,761
everything is going to be okay.

747
01:33:21,262 --> 01:33:23,389
Everything is going to go back to normal.

748
01:33:38,154 --> 01:33:39,322
Trust me, Renta.

749
01:34:41,759 --> 01:34:45,846
I AM SORRY, BAR. I HAVE TO GO.

750
01:34:45,930 --> 01:34:48,724
I JUST WISH FOR ONE THING.
FINISH YOUR STORIES.

751
01:36:23,527 --> 01:36:26,280
{\an8}MIA, THE GIRL NEXT DOOR, LISTENS TO,
NOT ONLY MY GUITAR OR MY STORIES

752
01:36:26,363 --> 01:36:29,325
{\an8}BUT ALSO TO RENTA'S AND MY DESIRES
AND THOUGHTS. MIA IS TRULY A WOMAN.

753
01:36:39,543 --> 01:36:40,711
How did you get in here?

754
01:36:41,212 --> 01:36:43,923
Your description of me
is really interesting, Bar.

755
01:36:52,431 --> 01:36:53,557
This is Renta's key!

756
01:36:54,433 --> 01:36:55,768
Where did you get it?

757
01:36:56,310 --> 01:36:57,645
What have you done to her?

758
01:37:41,522 --> 01:37:42,648
Where is Renta?

759
01:37:43,691 --> 01:37:44,900
Where is she?

760
01:37:45,401 --> 01:37:49,154
It turns out that the most interesting
story of all is your own story, Bar.

761
01:37:53,075 --> 01:37:54,702
What have you done to her?

762
01:38:18,601 --> 01:38:21,312
Please, Mia, where is she?

763
01:38:55,137 --> 01:38:57,014
<i>I thought this block had nine floors?</i>

764
01:38:59,475 --> 01:39:00,809
<i>The ninth floor is empty.</i>

765
01:39:02,061 --> 01:39:04,563
<i>-It's haunted.</i>
-<i>Really?</i>

766
01:39:05,064 --> 01:39:08,525
<i>People say that the ninth floor</i>
<i>is haunted by the ghosts of people</i>

767
01:39:09,026 --> 01:39:10,653
<i>whose houses caught fire.</i>

768
01:39:11,904 --> 01:39:15,240
<i>The building is built over the remains.</i>

769
01:39:17,201 --> 01:39:19,286
Renta!

770
01:40:21,598 --> 01:40:23,100
Help!

771
01:40:47,416 --> 01:40:48,459
Sir, please help.

772
01:41:09,104 --> 01:41:11,648
And how is this story going to end?

773
01:41:20,616 --> 01:41:22,534
Everything happens for a reason.

774
01:42:44,241 --> 01:42:47,786
CIKINI BOOKSTORE

775
01:43:10,934 --> 01:43:15,439
FICTION.
BY BARI ANDHARA

